The chief of the European Commission later met President Volodymyr Zelensky in Kyiv and handed him a questionnaire that will kick-start the formal application. Speaking at a news conference, she said he could expect a decision "in weeks" if he applied. He replied he would do so within a week. Earlier Ms von der Leyen was ashen-faced as she spoke during a visit to Bucha, a suburb of Kyiv. Standing beside bodies exhumed from a mass grave of hundreds by forensic investigators, she said: "The unthinkable has happened here. We have seen the cruel face of Putin's army. We have seen the recklessness and the coldheartedness with which they have been occupying the city." 